{
  "doc_id": "43068",
  "text": "In Britain, dietary patterns during pregnancy have been described by two cohort studies [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] but neither have yet reported associations with childhood body composition. Diet patterns in children have been described in other cohort studies [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] and a recent review concluded that childhood dietary patterns consisting of energy dense, high fat and low fibre foods were positively associated with obesity [CITATION_7] .",
